-- Turkish banks' Jan-July profit down 12.6 percent- banking watchdog
-- By Ece Toksabay
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 07:42AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 29 (Reuters) - The Turkish banking sector's net profit fell 12.6 percent year-on-year to 14.5 billion lira ($6.71 billion) in the first seven months of the year, the banking watchdog BDDK said on Friday.

The sector's loans stood at 1.14 trillion lira at the end July, watchdog data showed.